  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 22:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ὁ Θεὸς τῶν πατέρων ἡμῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the God of our fathers",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 3:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", note [a frequent appellation in the Acts above the other books of the New Testament, appropriate to that time, when the promises made to “the fathers” were being fulfilled].—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "προεχειρίσατό σε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "hath appointed thee",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [beforehand]) Ananias affirms that this vision was vouchsafed to Paul as an act of grace, not in wrath.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὸ θέλημα αὐτοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "His will",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", a righteous will, which is set forth in Christ: ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 20:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 6:38-39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἰδεῖν τὸν Δίκαιον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to see the Just One",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") An extraordinary benefit. Christ, who was always just (righteous), is now also altogether exempt even from the sin of others, which had been imposed on Him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 9:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Since His having gone to the Father, as our “Advocate” or Paraclete, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 2:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", we do not now see Him, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 16:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : and yet He was beheld by Paul. Moreover He is the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Just",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " One, because He fulfilled all the will of the Father in (by) Himself, and fulfils it in us. This His justice, or righteousness, is the sum of the Gospel, of which Paul is made the witness. Paul also afterwards saw this Just One: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 22:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 26:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 14.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
