        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Hath appointed thee",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "προεχειρίσατό σε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", a word found in the New Testament only here and in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 26:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 3:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (R.T.). In classical Greek it means mostly \"to get anything ready beforehand;\" to cause anything to be ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "πρόχειρος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ready to hand. And in the LXX. it means \"to choose,\" or \"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "appoint",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",\" as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 3:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 4:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where it is not a translation of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "שְׁלַח",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but a paraphrase of the sentence, \"Appoint one by whom thou wilt send.\" Here it may be rendered indifferently either \"choose\" or \"appoint.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The Righteous One",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The designation of Messiah in such passages as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 53:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 72:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. (see in the New Testament ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 23:47",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 2:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 19:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.). A voice from his mouth is a very awkward though literal rendering. The A.V. expresses the sense much better. Acts 22:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
